cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the analysis of photographic style attributes using deep learning methods. The primary focus is on the composition of photographs, which is a key aspect of computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation strategies, which is a common technique in machine learning and deep learning. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper proposes a novel input representation and a two-column CNN architecture, which are both related to machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with geometric properties and vanishing lines, which are related to computer graphics and geometry. Therefore, the paper could also belong to cs.GR (Computer Graphics).
